{"key":"post-8507302","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>8507302</id>\n<content>If you add a dry powder to a wet substance such as hydrated grains, it sticks to the first kernels it lands on and doesn't move.&amp;nbsp; In addition, it will absorb moisture, throwing off your mix.&amp;nbsp; Add gypsum at the soak stage and stir well.&amp;nbsp; Stir well again as you simmer and the gypsum will coat all the grains.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next></next>\n<prev>8507278</prev>\n<first>8504134</first>\n<last>8507302</last>\n<when>1213124122</when>\n<utime>06/10/08 09:55 PM</utime>\n</post>"}